Cocktail Paradise

Cocktail Paradise is a web application that allows users to search for cocktails and view detailed information about them in an interactive and user-friendly interface. It uses TheCocktailDB API to fetch cocktail data dynamically.

Features

1. Search Functionality

Users can search for cocktails by name using a search bar.

Displays a grid of matching cocktails based on the search query.

2. Cocktail Grid

Dynamically displays cocktail cards fetched from TheCocktailDB API.

Each card includes a thumbnail image and the cocktail's name.

3. Modal View

Clicking on a cocktail card opens a modal with detailed information, including:

Ingredients and measurements.

Preparation instructions.

A larger image of the cocktail.

4. Responsive Design

The application is fully responsive and works seamlessly on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.


Open the index.html file in your preferred web browser.

Usage

Search for a Cocktail

Enter the name of a cocktail (e.g., "Margarita") in the search bar.

Click the Search button or press Enter.

The cocktail grid will display matching results.

View Cocktail Details

Click on a cocktail card to open the modal.

View the ingredients, instructions, and a larger image of the cocktail.

Close the modal by clicking the close button (X) or clicking outside the modal content.



Technologies Used

HTML5: For the structure of the web application.

CSS3: For styling and responsive design.

JavaScript (ES6+): For interactivity and dynamic functionality.

TheCocktailDB API: For fetching cocktail data.

Known Issues and Improvements

Known Issues:

If a query returns no results, the grid displays a "No results found" message.

Modal behavior may vary slightly across browsers.

Potential Improvements:

Add pagination for large result sets.

Include filtering options (e.g., by ingredients, alcohol content).

Improve modal accessibility with ARIA attributes.

